history.content:
Usually, you will need enrollment permission in the form of an enrollment code from the instructor. Often, this won't happen until close to or even after the semester starts. In a normal semester I'd recommend attending the first class to find out enrollment details if all else fails, but not super sure how to go about this in the online format -- you would probably have to get in touch with the professor. I personally wouldn't be too worried about this right now since it's still fairly early.

Also, if you are an undergrad, I believe the reason you're seeing that message is because you're an undergrad (not major related).

I was wondering what the process is for enrolling in an EE graduate class (227C in particular) for which I have all the necessary prerequisites. When I tried signing up for it directly, the message I get is "Permission to enroll in this class is required. The class falls outside your career of study. Choose another class," and this is likely because I am in L&S CS. I tried emailing the professor for the course, but I got no response. As a result, I'm not really sure what I should do to enroll (or even if it is possible to do so) - can anyone offer any advice/experience?

Thanks a lot!
history.subject: Enrolling in an EE Graduate Class
